## 5. System Infrastructure (`utils/` & Environment)

* **`config_manager.py`:** Handles the local persistence layer via `~/.qekit_config.json`. This stores environment variables such as global pseudopotential library paths, system execution profiles, and default operational paths.
* **`build_pseudo_lib.py`:** A web-scraping package downloader. It parses official online pseudopotential databases, extracts functional files (PBE/LDA/NC), automatically classifies them by analyzing internal nomenclature strings, and deposits them into a structured file hierarchy:

```text
~/QE-POTCAR/
├── PBE/
│   ├── scalar/
│   │   ├── PAW/
│   │   └── USPP/
│   └── full/
└── LDA/

```

* **Terminal Interface & Headless Mode:** Built on `questionary`, implementing a highly legible, color-coded, keyboard-navigable workflow using distinct University of Dhaka visual signatures. The application features full command-line flag handling (e.g., `qekit --206`, `--304`) to facilitate completely headless batch job scripts.

