## 6. Project Architecture

The codebase maintains a strictly modular structure, separating visual rendering tasks, infrastructure layers, and physical computations cleanly:

```text
QE-Kit/
├── qekit.py                  # Master CLI Orchestrator & Entry Point
├── pyproject.toml            # Metadata, Dependency, and Script Mapping
├── MANIFEST.in               # Configuration to bundle Bash/Asset additions
├── modules/                  # Computation & Physics Generation Engines
│   ├── __init__.py
│   ├── structure2in.py       # Structural ingestion (ASE backend)
│   ├── pseudo_select.py      # Automated UPF mapping
│   ├── build_pseudo_lib.py   # Scraper/downloader engine
│   ├── scf_gen.py            # Ground-state input builder
│   ├── optical_proc.py       # Optoelectronic tensor derivation
│   ├── epc_processor.py      # Eliashberg/$T_c$ analytics
│   └── ...
└── utils/                    # Data infrastructure & Plotting routines
    ├── __init__.py
    ├── config_manager.py     # JSON state manager
    ├── bz_plotter.py         # 3D Brillouin Zone visualizer
    ├── xrd_plotter.py        # Simulated XRD renderer
    ├── ht_phonon.sh          # Phonon automated chain script
    └── ...

```

